00:16:11.370 --> 00:16:13.276
Look for anyone who's
posted about or with

269
00:16:13.300 --> 00:16:14.946
- a Peter and Debbie dummy.
- On it.

270
00:16:14.970 --> 00:16:15.986
Keep us posted. ok?

271
00:16:16.010 --> 00:16:17.570
Ok. get you something when I have it.

272
00:17:28.280 --> 00:17:30.456
Got another one. Gary. Indiana.

273
00:17:30.480 --> 00:17:32.196
Me too. Galveston. Texas.

274
00:17:32.220 --> 00:17:34.456
But none of them are Peter or Debbies.

275
00:17:34.480 --> 00:17:35.696
All right. get me addresses.

276
00:17:35.720 --> 00:17:37.366
I'll send the black and
whites to keep a lookout.

277
00:17:37.390 --> 00:17:39.686
I had no idea so many
people had talking dolls.

278
00:17:39.710 --> 00:17:41.336
- Figures.
- What does?

279
00:17:41.360 --> 00:17:45.536
No. the community prefers
the term figures over dolls.

280
00:17:47.490 --> 00:17:49.166
- Crud.
- What is it?

281
00:17:49.190 --> 00:17:51.316
A woman named Jane
hines was just found shot dead

282
00:17:51.340 --> 00:17:53.036
in her home 20 minutes
from Fletcher's shop.

283
00:17:53.060 --> 00:17:54.206
Is it our guy?

284
00:17:54.230 --> 00:17:56.216
He was carrying a wooden figure.

285
00:17:56.240 --> 00:17:57.616
Yeah. that'll do it.

286
00:17:57.640 --> 00:17:58.786
All right. get this to bex.

287
00:17:58.810 --> 00:18:00.326
I'll call the locals and
give them a heads up

288
00:18:00.350 --> 00:18:01.926
that the team's on the way.

289
00:18:17.720 --> 00:18:19.946
Jane didn't have any enemies.

290
00:18:19.970 --> 00:18:22.306
Everyone loved my sister.

291
00:18:22.330 --> 00:18:24.070
I'm sure they did. ma'am.

292
00:18:25.760 --> 00:18:27.236
Y'all must be the feds.

293
00:18:27.260 --> 00:18:28.566
We heard you were coming.

294
00:18:28.590 --> 00:18:30.376
Yeah. your sergeant already briefed us.

295
00:18:30.400 --> 00:18:32.316
We'll take it from here.

296
00:18:32.340 --> 00:18:34.486
I'm sorry for your loss. ma'am.

297
00:18:38.100 --> 00:18:39.756
Why don't you give me a minute?

298
00:18:39.780 --> 00:18:41.120
Sure. yeah.

299
00:18:44.880 --> 00:18:46.666
It's kari. right?

300
00:18:46.690 --> 00:18:48.026
Yes.

301
00:18:48.050 --> 00:18:49.776
Do you mind if I ask
you a couple questions?

302
00:18:49.800 --> 00:18:51.086
Of course.

303
00:18:51.110 --> 00:18:54.106
But I don't know anything.

304
00:18:54.130 --> 00:18:55.836
You might know more than you think.

305
00:18:58.730 --> 00:19:02.416
This might sound odd.
but did your sister own

306
00:19:02.440 --> 00:19:05.346
any dolls made by a man
named Nicholas Fletcher?

307
00:19:05.370 --> 00:19:06.946
A doll?

308
00:19:06.970 --> 00:19:08.356
No.

309
00:19:08.380 --> 00:19:11.016
Jane really wasn't the doll type.

310
00:19:14.520 --> 00:19:16.070
What is it?

311
00:19:17.990 --> 00:19:21.636
Well. that name. Nicholas Fletcher...

312
00:19:21.660 --> 00:19:24.786
I've heard it before.

313
00:19:27.900 --> 00:19:29.516
It's Lazarus.

314
00:19:29.540 --> 00:19:31.376
Says she leaves for DC tomorrow.

315
00:19:31.400 --> 00:19:33.000
but she's down for dinner tonight

316
00:19:33.110 --> 00:19:34.886
if we make it back in time.

317
00:19:34.910 --> 00:19:36.746
Well. sounds like she's taking the bait.

318
00:19:36.770 --> 00:19:38.916
- Nice work.
- Hey.

319
00:19:38.940 --> 00:19:41.856
So turns out Jane didn't own a dummy.

320
00:19:41.880 --> 00:19:43.926
she was the inspiration for one.

321
00:19:43.950 --> 00:19:45.356
What?

322
00:19:45.380 --> 00:19:47.266
According to the sister. she
met Nicholas at a county fair.

323
00:19:47.290 --> 00:19:49.266
and he asked if she would
model for one of the dummies.

324
00:19:49.290 --> 00:19:52.066
Debbie the dummy is based on Jane.

325
00:19:52.090 --> 00:19:53.736
I don't know why. but
that makes all of this

326
00:19:53.760 --> 00:19:55.066
a lot creepier.

327
00:19:55.090 --> 00:19:57.226
So maybe Dylan shows
up. looking to meet

328
00:19:57.250 --> 00:19:58.796
the real-life version of his doll.

329
00:19:58.820 --> 00:20:00.656
He freaks her out. things
go bad. and he kills her.

330
00:20:00.680 --> 00:20:02.416
I mean. if a guy's showing
up at my front doorstep

331
00:20:02.440 --> 00:20:03.716
saying he lived in a missile silo

332
00:20:03.740 --> 00:20:05.976
for eight years playing
with a doll version of me.

333
00:20:06.000 --> 00:20:07.716
yeah. I think he might be nuts.

334
00:20:07.740 --> 00:20:09.086
Yeah. sure.

335
00:20:09.110 --> 00:20:11.116
But if Jane rejected
him or called him crazy.

336
00:20:11.140 --> 00:20:13.486
why didn't he beat her like
he did all the other victims

337
00:20:13.510 --> 00:20:14.826
who humiliated him?

338
00:20:14.850 --> 00:20:16.316
No. you're right.

339
00:20:16.340 --> 00:20:18.416
Shooting her in the head is
perfunctory. not rage-driven.

340
00:20:18.440 --> 00:20:21.496
But even if Dylan just came
here looking for answers.

341
00:20:21.520 --> 00:20:23.536
how did he even know
about this woman?

342
00:20:23.560 --> 00:20:26.266
I spoke to Ronnie.
Nicholas Fletcher's assistant.

343
00:20:26.290 --> 00:20:28.596
Apparently what makes
every Nicholas Fletcher dummy

344
00:20:28.620 --> 00:20:30.296
so special is the fact that they're

345
00:20:30.320 --> 00:20:32.406
all based off of real people.

346
00:20:32.430 --> 00:20:34.366
That ledger wasn't just a bill of sales.

347
00:20:34.390 --> 00:20:37.346
it had a record of every real
person whose likeness he used.

348
00:20:37.370 --> 00:20:39.086
And now Dylan has that too.

349
00:20:39.110 --> 00:20:41.086
Ok. so if Jane is the basis
for the Debbie dummy.

350
00:20:41.110 --> 00:20:43.306
then we need to figure out
who the inspiration for Peter is.

351
00:20:43.330 --> 00:20:45.256
That's where he's going next.

352
00:20:51.540 --> 00:20:55.396
I actually like you a lot more now. Jeff.

353
00:20:58.220 --> 00:21:02.266
- So was it love at first sight?
- Pretty much.

354
00:21:02.290 --> 00:21:04.496
I asked Nicholas Fletcher very nicely

355
00:21:04.520 --> 00:21:06.106
to make me another Peter doll.

356
00:21:07.430 --> 00:21:09.946
And he still refused.

357
00:21:09.970 --> 00:21:13.546
Are you gonna let me
go when you're done?

358
00:21:13.570 --> 00:21:16.306
Please. talk to me.

359
00:21:20.870 --> 00:21:24.086
That scar is new.

360
00:21:24.110 --> 00:21:26.656
What happened?

361
00:21:26.680 --> 00:21:28.826
R-Rock climbing.

362
00:21:30.120 --> 00:21:31.366
Interesting.

363
00:21:31.390 --> 00:21:33.656
I hear it's very dangerous.

364
00:21:43.140 --> 00:21:45.886
Please. stay still.

365
00:21:45.910 --> 00:21:49.686
Peter needs to look just like you.

366
00:21:53.580 --> 00:21:55.426
Hey. You get something?

367
00:21:55.450 --> 00:21:57.616
Yeah. speaking to Fletcher's
assistant got me thinking.

368
00:21:57.640 --> 00:21:59.666
So I checked into Jane's finances.

369
00:21:59.690 --> 00:22:01.586
Smart. And?

370
00:22:01.610 --> 00:22:03.526
And in Jane's bank statement.

371
00:22:03.550 --> 00:22:05.896
I found a $500 money
order that Fletcher sent

372
00:22:05.920 --> 00:22:07.466
to her back in 2015.

373
00:22:07.490 --> 00:22:08.966
- So we can now then go...
- already did.

374
00:22:08.990 --> 00:22:10.536
Here are all the money orders

375
00:22:10.560 --> 00:22:11.636
that Nicholas Fletcher ever sent.

376
00:22:11.660 --> 00:22:13.956
And here are who he sent them to.

377
00:22:13.980 --> 00:22:15.576
Morales. can you enlarge

378
00:22:15.600 --> 00:22:18.136
four in. second row from the bottom?

379
00:22:18.160 --> 00:22:21.646
Kind of looks like the Peter doll. right?

380
00:22:21.670 --> 00:22:22.956
Keith Jones.

381
00:22:22.980 --> 00:22:24.756
Looks like he's a Nebraska native.

382
00:22:24.780 --> 00:22:26.326
Lives just over the Wyoming
state line in scottsbluff.

383
00:22:26.350 --> 00:22:28.416
I'll tell the team.

384
00:22:28.440 --> 00:22:30.146
Then get your gun.

385
00:22:30.170 --> 00:22:31.586
You too. Ben.

386
00:22:31.610 --> 00:22:33.266
We're way closer than bex and the team.

387
00:22:33.290 --> 00:22:35.066
I'll tell them we got this.

388
00:22:57.110 --> 00:22:59.576
Ben.

389
00:23:45.820 --> 00:23:48.226
Looks like Dylan took off.

390
00:23:48.250 --> 00:23:49.496
Gun!

391
00:24:06.100 --> 00:24:07.256
Peck's hit.

392
00:24:07.280 --> 00:24:08.286
Which way?

393
00:24:08.310 --> 00:24:09.756
He went out the back.

394
00:24:09.780 --> 00:24:11.626
You're gonna be ok.

395
00:24:11.650 --> 00:24:12.816
Just hang in there. John.

396
00:24:12.840 --> 00:24:14.896
We're gonna get you to a hospital.

397
00:24:16.780 --> 00:24:18.246
You got this.

398
00:24:27.800 --> 00:24:28.906
Dylan's in the wind.

399
00:24:28.930 --> 00:24:30.516
He had a car stashed out back.

400
00:24:30.540 --> 00:24:32.176
I lost him. How is he?

401
00:24:32.200 --> 00:24:33.816
He needs a hospital.

402
00:24:33.840 --> 00:24:35.446
Hep me get him outside.

403
00:24:37.040 --> 00:24:38.256
Ok.

404
00:24:38.280 --> 00:24:39.576
We passed a hospital in bluff side.

405
00:24:39.600 --> 00:24:40.600
just a few miles back.

406
00:24:40.650 --> 00:24:41.926
Stay here. Secure the scene.

407
00:24:41.950 --> 00:24:43.296
Tell bex and the guys what happened.

408
00:24:43.320 --> 00:24:44.916
We need to find Dylan.

409
00:24:47.890 --> 00:24:49.196
Ok.

410
00:24:49.220 --> 00:24:51.066
One sec.

411
00:24:51.090 --> 00:24:52.866
- Yo.
- Can you guys see me ok?

412
00:24:52.890 --> 00:24:54.396
Yeah. we got you. Ben. What's up?

413
00:24:54.420 --> 00:24:56.476
- What happened?
- Dylan ambushed us.

414
00:24:56.500 --> 00:24:57.976
Keith was dead before we got here.

415
00:24:58.000 --> 00:24:59.206
- and peck got shot.
- What?

416
00:24:59.230 --> 00:25:00.446
- Is he ok?
- Where did he get hit?

417
00:25:00.470 --> 00:25:01.636
Bullet clipped him in the side.

418
00:25:01.660 --> 00:25:02.766
He was bleeding a lot.

419
00:25:02.790 --> 00:25:03.990
Ok. Why aren't you with him?

420
00:25:04.040 --> 00:25:05.416
Morales is taking him to the hospital.

421
00:25:05.440 --> 00:25:06.886
She asked me to stay
behind and walk you

422
00:25:06.910 --> 00:25:08.476
- through the crime scene.
- Love that woman.

423
00:25:08.500 --> 00:25:09.976
All right. give it to us.

424
00:25:10.000 --> 00:25:11.416
You seeing all this?

425
00:25:13.170 --> 00:25:14.356
What's that?

426
00:25:14.380 --> 00:25:15.786
- What?
- No. back.

427
00:25:15.810 --> 00:25:17.716
The box on the table. Yeah.

428
00:25:17.740 --> 00:25:19.916
It looks like a doll-making kit.

429
00:25:19.940 --> 00:25:21.996
Eyeballs. paint...

430
00:25:22.020 --> 00:25:24.896
Dylan stole it from
Nicholas Fletcher's shop.

431
00:25:24.920 --> 00:25:27.596
He's remaking the dummies.

432
00:25:27.620 --> 00:25:28.766
He lost Peter and Debbie in the blast.

433
00:25:28.790 --> 00:25:30.476
so now he's visiting the inspirations

434
00:25:30.500 --> 00:25:32.176
that they were based on
in order to remake them.

435
00:25:32.200 --> 00:25:33.636
I mean. look at the kit.

436
00:25:33.660 --> 00:25:35.966
You don't lug that around
unless you're using it.

437
00:25:35.990 --> 00:25:37.716
There were some unfinished.
blank-faced dummies

438
00:25:37.740 --> 00:25:38.876
at the workshop.

439
00:25:38.900 --> 00:25:40.306
That's why he went there.

440
00:25:40.330 --> 00:25:41.646
So now he's got the dummy.
the dummy-making kit.

441
00:25:41.670 --> 00:25:43.516
He's remade Peter and Debbie.

442
00:25:43.540 --> 00:25:45.756
Ok. he's got his dolls. so
where does he go next?

443
00:25:45.780 --> 00:25:47.686
And why smash up the place?

444
00:25:47.710 --> 00:25:49.426
I mean. look at that TV.

445
00:25:49.450 --> 00:25:51.656
Looks like he's used
it as a punching bag.

446
00:25:51.680 --> 00:25:54.326
What are those videos on the ground?

447
00:25:54.350 --> 00:25:56.796
It seems like a mixed
bag of comedy shows.

448
00:25:56.820 --> 00:26:00.236
solo performances. bootleg specials.

449
00:26:00.260 --> 00:26:02.866
how-to comedian videos.

450
00:26:02.890 --> 00:26:04.306
Wait. no. back it up.

451
00:26:04.330 --> 00:26:07.036
That open DVD. what is that?

452
00:26:07.060 --> 00:26:10.346
"Live with Jeff Miller and Mr. Bonkers:

453
00:26:10.370 --> 00:26:12.116
A killer good time."

454
00:26:12.140 --> 00:26:14.306
You don't think Jeff modeled Mr. Bonkers

455
00:26:14.330 --> 00:26:16.476
after Dylan. do you?

456
00:26:16.500 --> 00:26:18.876
That's exactly what I think.

457
00:26:18.900 --> 00:26:20.186
Hi. everybody.

458
00:26:20.210 --> 00:26:22.086
I'm Jeff. and this is
my friend. Mr. Bonkers.

459
00:26:22.110 --> 00:26:23.456
Come on out. Mr. Bonkers.

460
00:26:23.480 --> 00:26:25.696
- Say hi.
- I don't wanna.

461
00:26:25.720 --> 00:26:26.986
Why not?

462
00:26:27.010 --> 00:26:28.496
What's there to be afraid of?

463
00:26:28.520 --> 00:26:31.126
It's just so humiliating.

464
00:26:31.150 --> 00:26:32.336
What?

465
00:26:32.360 --> 00:26:33.866
Nobody's gonna laugh at you.

466
00:26:33.890 --> 00:26:36.690
I know. That's the trouble.

467
00:26:36.800 --> 00:26:39.636
No one laughs.

468
00:26:39.660 --> 00:26:43.846
- Well...
- but if I can't kill 'em with comedy.

469
00:26:43.870 --> 00:26:46.716
I'll hammer home the humor.

470
00:26:52.680 --> 00:26:54.326
That's a bit violent. isn't it?

471
00:26:54.350 --> 00:26:55.556
And?

472
00:26:55.580 --> 00:26:57.056
Well. you can't just go
around killing people.

473
00:26:57.080 --> 00:26:58.456
Why not?

474
00:26:58.480 --> 00:27:03.066
How do you think I got
these nifty striped pajamas?

475
00:27:05.690 --> 00:27:08.636
I'm guessing Dylan wasn't
too flattered about this.

476
00:27:08.660 --> 00:27:10.676
Nope. It's the ultimate form of heckling.

477
00:27:10.700 --> 00:27:13.006
If anything could trigger
Dylan's rage. it'd be this.

478
00:27:13.030 --> 00:27:14.446
So he gets out of the pit.

479
00:27:14.470 --> 00:27:16.346
finds out that another
comic got famous using him

480
00:27:16.370 --> 00:27:18.676
as the punchline.

481
00:27:21.070 --> 00:27:22.546
He's going after Jeff next.

482
00:27:28.780 --> 00:27:31.826
Well. here we are.

483
00:27:31.850 --> 00:27:34.296
Beautiful house.

484
00:27:34.320 --> 00:27:36.936
All that touring money. must be nice.

485
00:27:36.960 --> 00:27:39.036
You know. the first time
I ever saw the special.

486
00:27:39.060 --> 00:27:42.226
I was hiding out in a
shelter right after the blast.

487
00:27:42.250 --> 00:27:46.660
They had a goodwill
with all these $0.99 DVDs.

488
00:27:46.770 --> 00:27:49.376
My god. with the sob story.

489
00:27:49.400 --> 00:27:51.116
Why are we sitting on our asses?

490
00:27:51.140 --> 00:27:52.576
Be nice.

491
00:27:52.600 --> 00:27:55.046
Dylan needs time to process
everything. find his voice.

492
00:27:55.070 --> 00:27:56.786
I think he's changing his mind.

493
00:27:56.810 --> 00:27:57.956
I'm not.

494
00:27:57.980 --> 00:27:59.286
You're making the right decision.

495
00:27:59.310 --> 00:28:00.626
It's been a long time coming.

496
00:28:00.650 --> 00:28:03.556
This guy's gonna get what he deserves.

497
00:28:03.580 --> 00:28:05.196
What do you think. Dr. Debbie?

498
00:28:05.220 --> 00:28:07.096
It's like I always say. Dylan.

499
00:28:07.120 --> 00:28:09.026
you need to make your own decisions.

500
00:28:09.050 --> 00:28:10.596
He's a hack.

501
00:28:17.030 --> 00:28:18.466
I want to hurt him.

502
00:28:18.490 --> 00:28:21.006
Then I think it's important
that you hurt him.

503
00:28:21.030 --> 00:28:23.336
I want him to feel exactly how I felt

504
00:28:23.360 --> 00:28:26.176
the first time I saw that video.

505
00:28:26.200 --> 00:28:28.300
Hey. Peter.

506
00:28:28.410 --> 00:28:29.886
Knock. knock.

507
00:28:29.910 --> 00:28:31.256
Who's there?

508
00:28:31.280 --> 00:28:32.816
I'm-a.

509
00:28:32.840 --> 00:28:34.286
I'm-a who?

510
00:28:37.840 --> 00:28:41.010
I'm-a go kill Jeff.

511
00:29:10.980 --> 00:29:12.996
Knock. knock.

512
00:29:14.310 --> 00:29:17.366
- You...
- no.

513
00:29:17.390 --> 00:29:18.836
That's not how the joke goes.

514
00:29:18.860 --> 00:29:20.836
You shouldn't be here.
I'm calling the cops.

515
00:29:22.790 --> 00:29:25.006
I saw your act. Jeff.

516
00:29:25.030 --> 00:29:27.006
I gotta say. I didn't laugh.

517
00:29:35.910 --> 00:29:36.906
Morales.

518
00:29:36.930 --> 00:29:38.246
Hey. bex.

519
00:29:38.270 --> 00:29:39.610
How's peck?

520
00:29:39.740 --> 00:29:41.126
He's still in surgery.

521
00:29:41.150 --> 00:29:42.956
He lost a lot of blood.

522
00:29:42.980 --> 00:29:45.020
I-I should have cleared
the whole house before I...

523
00:29:45.080 --> 00:29:46.586
hey. stop.

524
00:29:46.610 --> 00:29:48.766
Morales. none of this is your fault. ok?

525
00:29:48.790 --> 00:29:51.066
It was your quick thinking
in getting him to the hospital.

526
00:29:51.090 --> 00:29:53.536
that is the reason he's alive.

527
00:29:53.560 --> 00:29:54.866
Yeah.

528
00:29:54.890 --> 00:29:56.336
Yeah. ok.

529
00:29:58.800 --> 00:30:02.036
Look. I know that you
and peck are close. ok?

530
00:30:02.060 --> 00:30:04.436
When he comes out of
surgery. it's gonna be your face

531
00:30:04.460 --> 00:30:06.260
that he wants to see.

532
00:30:07.770 --> 00:30:09.810
Get this guy. bex.

533
00:30:12.210 --> 00:30:13.780
On it.

534
00:30:22.980 --> 00:30:25.636
It was a joke.

535
00:30:25.660 --> 00:30:27.906
I thought you were dead.

536
00:30:27.930 --> 00:30:32.106
Please. just take the dummy.

537
00:30:32.130 --> 00:30:33.670
Let me go.

538
00:30:37.790 --> 00:30:39.830
Stay still. please.

539
00:30:42.610 --> 00:30:45.310
I'll do anything you want.

540
00:30:45.440 --> 00:30:46.810
Anything.

541
00:30:51.950 --> 00:30:55.596
Jeff. meet dead Jeff.

542
00:31:00.630 --> 00:31:03.826
What do you think?

543
00:31:03.850 --> 00:31:06.106
You're insane.

544
00:31:06.130 --> 00:31:08.876
I don't think he likes us.

545
00:31:08.900 --> 00:31:11.316
Me neither.

546
00:31:11.340 --> 00:31:14.006
And I don't care.

547
00:31:14.030 --> 00:31:15.510
Me neither.

548
00:31:19.690 --> 00:31:21.700
Hey. guys. police just got to the scene.

549
00:31:21.840 --> 00:31:23.296
Dylan and Jeff are both gone.

550
00:31:23.320 --> 00:31:24.796
but there's clear evidence of a struggle.

551
00:31:24.820 --> 00:31:26.726
- Is there a body?
- No.

552
00:31:26.750 --> 00:31:28.180
And from the looks of it.

553
00:31:28.290 --> 00:31:29.690
this just became an abduction case.

554
00:31:41.200 --> 00:31:42.646
Come on.

555
00:31:42.670 --> 00:31:44.846
Get up.

556
00:31:44.870 --> 00:31:47.870
Please.

557
00:31:54.880 --> 00:31:56.960
I sent you the security
footage from Jeff's house.

558
00:31:57.050 --> 00:31:58.956
This is from 30 minutes ago.

559
00:31:58.980 --> 00:32:01.296
He's keeping Jeff alive?

560
00:32:01.320 --> 00:32:02.760
Well. he took him alive.

561
00:32:02.890 --> 00:32:04.636
Don't think the plan is
to keep him that way.

562
00:32:04.660 --> 00:32:06.736
Question is. what is
he gonna do with him?

563
00:32:06.760 --> 00:32:09.036
Ok. so Dylan's ultimate
trigger is humiliation.

564
00:32:09.060 --> 00:32:10.906
It makes sense that he's going after Jeff.

565
00:32:10.930 --> 00:32:12.886
With Keith and Jane.
their kills were pragmatic.

566
00:32:12.910 --> 00:32:14.066
He needed to remake his dummies.

567
00:32:14.090 --> 00:32:17.016
But Jeff is who he really wants.

568
00:32:17.040 --> 00:32:18.226
Jeff!

569
00:32:18.250 --> 00:32:20.286
I didn't know you were coming in tonight.

570
00:32:20.310 --> 00:32:22.146
Hey. are you ok?

571
00:32:24.380 --> 00:32:26.246
You don't have to do this.

572
00:32:26.270 --> 00:32:28.186
Ok. well. if this is about humiliation

573
00:32:28.210 --> 00:32:30.110
like his other kills. then I would say

574
00:32:30.240 --> 00:32:32.120
he's planning something public.

575
00:32:32.250 --> 00:32:34.226
For that. he'll need an audience.

576
00:32:48.090 --> 00:32:50.436
Hello. folks. It's good to be back.

577
00:32:50.460 --> 00:32:52.876
We're gonna start the
show a little early tonight.

578
00:33:02.780 --> 00:33:05.396
I want to introduce you to someone.

579
00:33:05.420 --> 00:33:07.776
This is dead Jeff.

580
00:33:12.290 --> 00:33:13.286
Hey. Jeff.

581
00:33:13.310 --> 00:33:14.966
Looks like you had a rough night.

582
00:33:14.990 --> 00:33:16.436
You should see the other guy.

583
00:33:23.130 --> 00:33:24.916
All right. Ben. what do you got?

584
00:33:24.940 --> 00:33:26.886
There are 12 dedicated comedy clubs

585
00:33:26.910 --> 00:33:28.186
in the greater Denver area

586
00:33:28.210 --> 00:33:30.510
and another 18 venues
promoting open mics tonight.

587
00:33:30.640 --> 00:33:32.146
We don't have time to check them all.

588
00:33:32.170 --> 00:33:34.526
Wait. they both performed
at a place in Boulder called

589
00:33:34.550 --> 00:33:36.816
the Colorado comedy club back in 2015.

590
00:33:36.840 --> 00:33:38.656
And it looks like a few years ago.

591
00:33:38.680 --> 00:33:39.840
Jeff Miller bought it.

592
00:33:45.120 --> 00:33:47.826
You know Jeff. I don't
think that was heaven.

593
00:33:47.850 --> 00:33:49.306
Go to hell.

594
00:33:54.860 --> 00:33:58.210
How many of you
recognize my friend here?

595
00:33:58.340 --> 00:34:00.546
Who knows who dead Jeff is based on?

596
00:34:00.570 --> 00:34:02.006
Jeff Miller.

597
00:34:02.030 --> 00:34:03.506
You got it.

598
00:34:03.530 --> 00:34:05.676
This is dead Jeff Miller.

599
00:34:05.700 --> 00:34:07.290
You're hilarious.

600
00:34:10.030 --> 00:34:11.956
But. you know. really.
I should rename you

601
00:34:11.980 --> 00:34:14.026
not dead yet Jeff.

602
00:34:14.050 --> 00:34:15.796
But what do you think?

603
00:34:15.820 --> 00:34:17.190
Should I kill him?

604
00:34:20.730 --> 00:34:22.336
I'm serious.

605
00:34:22.360 --> 00:34:25.136
Who here thinks I should kill Jeff?

606
00:34:28.400 --> 00:34:31.400
I don't. Does that count?

607
00:34:34.560 --> 00:34:35.946
No.

608
00:34:35.970 --> 00:34:37.370
Come on.

609
00:34:37.480 --> 00:34:39.156
Jeff "the dud" Miller got famous

610
00:34:39.180 --> 00:34:40.556
off an act that wasn't his.

611
00:34:40.580 --> 00:34:41.740
He stole it.

612
00:34:41.870 --> 00:34:43.410
Did you all know that?

613
00:34:43.540 --> 00:34:45.996
Mr. Bonkers?

614
00:34:46.020 --> 00:34:47.826
Please.

615
00:34:47.850 --> 00:34:49.720
I say we kill him.

616
00:34:54.660 --> 00:34:56.506
Should I do it?

617
00:34:56.530 --> 00:34:58.166
Whoo!

618
00:34:59.860 --> 00:35:01.576
Yeah?

619
00:35:01.600 --> 00:35:03.730
No. no. don't do it!

620
00:35:33.770 --> 00:35:35.346
Hey. watch your background.

621
00:35:35.370 --> 00:35:36.846
It's full of friendlies in there.

622
00:35:36.870 --> 00:35:38.716
Copy that. I'll circle around the front.

623
00:35:41.740 --> 00:35:44.480
Yeah. all right.

624
00:35:47.710 --> 00:35:49.086
That was just the warm-up.

625
00:35:49.110 --> 00:35:50.810
Buckle up. everyone.

626
00:35:58.480 --> 00:35:59.596
I'm calling the cops.

627
00:35:59.620 --> 00:36:02.126
- This isn't funny.
- I disagree.

628
00:36:02.150 --> 00:36:04.476
I think it's hilarious.

629
00:36:07.170 --> 00:36:08.606
FBI. drop your weapon!

630
00:36:08.630 --> 00:36:10.346
- Everyone out! Get out.
- Get out the nearest exit.

631
00:36:10.370 --> 00:36:11.706
Keep your head low. Stay calm.

632
00:36:11.730 --> 00:36:13.466
Keep your heads down. Keep moving.

633
00:36:13.490 --> 00:36:14.686
You're all right. just keep moving.

634
00:36:14.710 --> 00:36:16.956
Get out. Everybody out.

635
00:36:16.980 --> 00:36:18.656
It's over. Dylan.

636
00:36:18.680 --> 00:36:20.256
You made your point. ok?

637
00:36:20.280 --> 00:36:22.156
- Let him go.
- My point?

638
00:36:22.180 --> 00:36:23.286
He's a hack.

639
00:36:23.310 --> 00:36:24.950
Got famous using me as a prop.

640
00:36:25.080 --> 00:36:26.996
And you wanted to
humiliate him in return. right?

641
00:36:27.020 --> 00:36:28.626
Well done. you did that.

642
00:36:28.650 --> 00:36:30.396
Just one more step.

643
00:36:30.420 --> 00:36:32.726
and I pop his head like a cherry.

644
00:36:32.750 --> 00:36:34.506
You're not gonna do that.

645
00:36:34.530 --> 00:36:36.006
Think about it. Dylan.

646
00:36:36.030 --> 00:36:37.496
What's worse than dying?

647
00:36:37.520 --> 00:36:39.036
Let him live with this.

648
00:36:39.060 --> 00:36:41.130
He's the idiot who got
humiliated on his own stage

649
00:36:41.270 --> 00:36:42.406
by his own dummy.

650
00:36:42.430 --> 00:36:44.446
He will never recover from that.

651
00:36:48.470 --> 00:36:52.346
You want to humiliate him forever?

652
00:36:52.370 --> 00:36:53.956
Don't kill him. Let him live.

653
00:36:56.550 --> 00:36:59.506
Dylan. put the gun down.

654
00:36:59.530 --> 00:37:01.220
You're right.

655
00:37:03.290 --> 00:37:05.066
My job is done.

656
00:37:05.090 --> 00:37:07.480
Hey. Jeff. what's red and full of holes?

657
00:37:09.190 --> 00:37:10.686
Me.

658
00:37:12.460 --> 00:37:14.846
No!

659
00:37:14.870 --> 00:37:16.446
Don't send me back.

660
00:37:16.470 --> 00:37:17.766
I got him. Shane. get the gun.

661
00:37:17.790 --> 00:37:18.900
Copy.

662
00:37:21.060 --> 00:37:23.546
- You ok?
- All right.

663
00:37:23.570 --> 00:37:25.116
- Yeah.
- You sure?

664
00:37:25.140 --> 00:37:26.616
- Thank you.
- Come on.

665
00:37:26.640 --> 00:37:28.356
Hey. Ben. we're gonna
need an ambulance.

666
00:37:28.380 --> 00:37:29.850
Copy. contacting dispatch.

667
00:37:29.980 --> 00:37:32.056
Eta ten minutes.

668
00:37:35.650 --> 00:37:36.920
Easy there.

669
00:37:39.120 --> 00:37:42.666
Those are some pretty heavy painkillers.

670
00:37:42.690 --> 00:37:45.226
These pills are good.

671
00:37:46.530 --> 00:37:49.546
Let's get you to bed before they wear off.

672
00:37:49.570 --> 00:37:51.110
That sounds nice.

673
00:37:53.270 --> 00:37:55.646
Have I told you how beautiful you are?

674
00:37:55.670 --> 00:37:57.586
Ok there. Casanova.

675
00:37:57.610 --> 00:37:59.686
You can tell me that when you're sober.

676
00:37:59.710 --> 00:38:01.056
Okay.

677
00:38:01.080 --> 00:38:03.526
Shane just sat down
to dinner with Lazarus.

678
00:38:03.550 --> 00:38:04.746
Got it.

679
00:38:04.770 --> 00:38:06.396
Find anything on Noah
Cyrus and the convoy?

680
00:38:06.420 --> 00:38:08.126
Nothing in there.

681
00:38:56.670 --> 00:38:58.276
Searched everything.

682
00:38:58.300 --> 00:38:59.746
This place is clean.

683
00:38:59.770 --> 00:39:02.136
Yeah. because she's too
smart to leave anything around

684
00:39:02.160 --> 00:39:03.586
for us to find.

685
00:39:08.500 --> 00:39:10.646
Getting shot hurts.

686
00:39:10.670 --> 00:39:12.456
I don't know what you expected.

687
00:39:12.480 --> 00:39:14.496
Here. let me help you.

688
00:39:14.520 --> 00:39:16.626
There we go.

689
00:39:19.670 --> 00:39:22.270
Hey. what happened here?

690
00:39:24.630 --> 00:39:26.970
You been out shooting
a rifle or something?

691
00:39:27.100 --> 00:39:29.676
Shh.

692
00:39:31.840 --> 00:39:33.986
But I-I thought that you said you...

693
00:39:34.010 --> 00:39:36.006
you didn't shoot.

694
00:39:36.030 --> 00:39:38.656
Secret stuff.

695
00:39:38.680 --> 00:39:40.526
What do you mean?

696
00:39:40.550 --> 00:39:43.220
We don't talk about missions.

697
00:40:14.400 --> 00:40:16.240
Tango down. All clear.

698
00:40:17.950 --> 00:40:19.496
In position.

699
00:40:22.550 --> 00:40:25.536
Breach. Breach.

700
00:40:34.600 --> 00:40:36.846
Target eliminated.
